Title: Adult three wheel bikes
text: One year ago, my wife and I bought two adult three wheel bicycles at the recommendation of my doctor. I have heart problems and needed more exercise, but I needed something with low impact on my knees and hips. After receiving the bikes, I found a challenge in putting them together. I‚Äôm 79 and my cognitive abilities are declining, and I became more and more frustrated as I struggled with the challenge. In the meantime, my health continued to decline, and the bikes sat in our garage or under cover on our patio. Hope springs eternal and I continued to hope we would be able to use the bikes at some point, but I am relegated to a walker or cane, so we have decided to sell the bikes. Our loss can be your gain. We will sell both bikes for the price of one. I have the invoice and we paid $747.02 for both bikes, including tax. One is Candy Apple Red and one is dark green. We will sell both bikes for $375.00 FIRM! Both bikes must go; we will not sell one bike at a time. You buy both bikes and you can sell one if you want to, but we want to be done with the issue. The ad on Amazon: Adult Tricycles, 3 Wheel Bikes for Adults 20/24/26 inch 7 Speed Adult Trikes Bicycles Cruise Trike with Shopping Basket for Seniors, Women, Men (Dark Red, 24" Wheels/7 Speed)

Title: Vintage Italjet Mini Bikes And Spares
text: This lot includes two complete motorcycles and lots of spare parts. The white bike is a 1991 Buster 2 that my son rode to victory at the 1992 World Mini. It starts and runs with a bit of fussing, but it has a broken fork spring. The other is a 70's MX50, I believe. I have not tried to get it running, but there is nothing wrong with the motor. It does, however, have serious grip rot. Both bikes are 50cc, Franco Morini S5 bottom ends, with centrifugal clutches. I don't have any parts specifically for the MX50, but the spare Buster engine and ignition parts fit both bikes. As the pictures show, there is a few years' accumulation of bits that will keep these bikes running. Many of these parts fit the early KTM and other Italian-made pee wee motors as well. I do not wish to separate, complete lot offered as is, reduced to $900.00 or best.  Thanks for your time!
